# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ML bundles, predictions, exports — ignore models/ except the triage bundle if you
# choose to commit it (optional). Corpus JSON / eval dumps stay local — not in git.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
models/*
!models/triage_bundle.joblib

# JSON data dumps (corpus predictions, extract_evaluation.json, semantic exports, etc.)
# Whitelist only standard JS/TS config files and the authored Case Studies content.
*.json
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!tsconfig.json
!jsconfig.json
# Case Studies authored content (read by the /case-studies tab and the /api/case-studies
# endpoint). Must ship with the deploy or Railway shows "No content yet."
!data/case_studies.json
# Q1 platform harm pipeline — authored + generated artifacts ship with deploy.
!ontology/q1/
!ontology/q1/*.json
# NOTE: data/case_study_notes.json is intentionally NOT whitelisted. It holds
# user-submitted community notes; committing it would overwrite live notes on every
# deploy. The loader returns [] when the file is absent, which is the correct default
# on Railway's ephemeral filesystem. Mount a volume or swap to the DB for durability.

# Serialized models / checkpoints (also covered by models/; these catch stray files)
*.joblib
!models/triage_bundle.joblib
*.jbl
*.pkl
*.pickle
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.h5
*.keras
*.npy
*.npz

# Keys / secrets
*.pem
*.key
credentials/
secrets/

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp

# Ontology merged graph caches (rebuilt locally / on Railway)
ontology/cache/
